# Auto commit and push

After finishing a coherent fix or feature in this repo, **commit and push to the current branch without waiting for the user to ask**.

## When to commit

- Bug fixes that resolve the reported issue
- Completed feature work the user requested
- Follow-up fixes to something just shipped in the same session

## How

- Follow the normal git safety protocol (status, diff, log; HEREDOC commit message; no force-push; no secrets)
- Stage only relevant source files (never `node_modules`, `.env`, credentials)
- Push to the tracked remote branch after a successful commit
- Brief confirmation in the reply (commit hash / message is enough)

## When not to

- User explicitly says not to commit or push
- Changes are exploratory, incomplete, or still waiting on a decision
- Only docs/rules/config noise with no related product change (unless the user asked for that)
